  "handbookAttendance": "<p>Jefferson High School places a high value on instructional time. Teachers and classmates depend on students to be in school on time to provide an uninterrupted classroom experience. When students have chronic unexcused absences or tardies, parents will receive a truancy notice and a conference will be scheduled.</p><h3>Reporting an Absence</h3><p>Parents are encouraged to call the JHS Attendance Office at <a href=\"tel:+16505507700\">(650) 550-7700</a> to excuse an absence or tardy on the morning the student will be absent or late. Advance notice is appreciated when possible.</p><p>Attendance notes must contain all of the following:</p><ul><li>Student's full name</li><li>Parent/legal guardian telephone number</li><li>Specific reason for absence (illness, doctor/dentist appointment, etc.)</li><li>Dates and/or periods absent</li><li>Signature of parent or legal guardian</li></ul><h3>Excused Absences (Ed Code 48205)</h3><p>Acceptable excuses include:</p><ul><li>Illness</li><li>Medical or dental appointments</li><li>Attendance at a funeral (1 day in California, up to 3 days out of state)</li><li>Court appearance</li><li>Observance of a religious holiday or ceremony (up to 4 days per year)</li></ul><p>Traffic delays and transportation difficulties are <strong>not</strong> excused absences under the Education Code. Please budget extra time on rainy mornings.</p><h3>Illness Limit (JUHSD Board Policy AR5113 B-C)</h3><p>Students may be excused as \"ILL\" no more than <strong>14 days</strong> in a school year. After the 14-day threshold, each illness absence must be accompanied by a <strong>note from a physician</strong> to be counted as excused. For ongoing health concerns, contact your student's counselor or health aide.</p><h3>Tardiness</h3><p>Students who are not in class when the bell rings must receive a pass from the attendance office or a staff member. Tardies are tracked and may result in discipline consequences such as detention.</p><h3>Hall Passes</h3><p>Students outside of their classroom during a class period must have a hall pass from their teacher. Passes should be used only for their intended purpose. Students should return to class as quickly as possible.</p>",
