  "handbookDistrictPolicies": "<h3>Bullying &amp; Harassment</h3><p>The Jefferson Union High School District encourages a positive attitude and does not tolerate bullying, teasing, taunting, or harassment of any kind. All staff and students should be treated with dignity and respect. Students are expected to speak courteously to others to ensure a safe and secure campus. Statements like \"I was just joking\" or \"I didn't really mean it\" do not excuse making others feel powerless. We cannot and do not condone this behavior.</p><p><strong>Bullying</strong> is an ongoing and deliberate misuse of power in relationships through repeated verbal, physical, and/or social behavior that intends to cause physical, social, and/or psychological harm.</p><h4>What to Do</h4><ol><li>Any student who feels they are being teased, taunted, harassed, or bullied — or any student who witnesses harassment or bullying — should give clear, direct feedback to the harasser/bully that the behavior is unwelcome.</li><li>If the bullying continues, report the behavior immediately to a teacher or other adult on campus.</li><li>If it continues to persist, or if it occurs outside of the classroom, immediately report this behavior to a teacher, counselor, or administrator.</li></ol><p>We encourage you to be an <strong>\"upstander\"</strong>, not a bystander — if you see bullying happening, take a stand against it by defending the victim, discouraging the bully, and reporting the incident.</p><h4>Types of Bullying &amp; Harassment</h4><table><thead><tr><th>Type</th><th>Examples</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Physical</strong></td><td>Hitting, kicking, pushing, biting, spitting, poking, throwing objects, taking personal belongings, unwanted tickling, etc.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Verbal</strong></td><td>Taunting, teasing to hurt someone's feelings, name-calling, threatening, gossiping, hurtful or harassing words, etc.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Psychological</strong></td><td>Spreading rumors (true or untrue), deliberately excluding someone from a group, extortion, intimidation, etc.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Sexual</strong></td><td>Exhibitionism, propositioning, sexual assault, physical contact of a sexual nature, sexually explicit comments/jokes/conversations, sexting, inappropriate drawings, etc.</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Cyber</strong></td><td>Verbal, psychological, and/or sexual bullying by electronic means including text messages, emails, social media posts, etc.</td></tr></tbody></table><h3>Sexual Harassment</h3><p><em>Please Note: All adults at JUHSD schools are mandated reporters. This means that for everyone's safety and security, information received by an adult that can harm you or others must be reported to school administration or a government agency to address the safety concern.</em></p><p>Prohibited sexual harassment includes, but is not limited to: unwelcome sexual advances, requests for sexual favors, and other verbal, visual, or physical conduct of a sexual nature.</p><p>Other types of conduct which constitute sexual harassment include:</p><ol><li>Unwelcome leering, sexual flirtations, or propositions</li><li>Unwelcome sexual slurs, verbal abuse, or sexually degrading descriptions</li><li>Graphic verbal comments about one's body</li><li>Sexual jokes, stories, drawings, pictures, or gestures</li><li>Spreading sexual rumors</li><li>Teasing or sexual remarks</li><li>Touching one's body or clothes in a sexual way</li><li>Cornering or blocking a person's normal movement</li><li>Displaying sexually aggressive objects on school property</li><li>Any act of retaliation upon an individual who reports a violation of district policy</li><li>Purposely limiting a student's access to educational tools due to the student's sexual orientation or preference</li><li>Information passed online via any electronic device or through social media that has a harmful effect on one's safety</li><li>An act or conversation any individual can hear that creates a hostile and unsafe learning environment</li></ol><p>Disciplinary actions taken for violation of this policy vary from warnings to referral to law enforcement.</p><h4>What Qualifies As Sexual Assault</h4><p>Sexual assault is any type of sexual contact or behavior that occurs without the explicit consent of the recipient.</p><h4>Who Do You Go To If You Feel You Are a Victim</h4><ul><li>The Principal or Vice Principals</li><li>Wellness Counselor or School Counselor</li><li>Student Welfare and Attendance Monitor</li><li>Any adult in the Main Office or Attendance Office</li><li>Any teacher on campus</li></ul><h4>Complaint Procedures</h4><p>All staff are encouraged to consider multiple approaches to report their concerns and complaints to the administration team. The district website has all complaint procedures listed at <a href='https://www.juhsd.net' target='_blank'>juhsd.net</a>.</p>",
